Note:
Strongly-typed integer widths for the Runa numeric primitive layer.

This module provides Int8/Int16/Int32/Int64/Int128 (signed) and
UInt8/UInt16/UInt32/UInt64/UInt128 (unsigned) along with the full
arithmetic, bitwise, comparison, conversion, and bit-manipulation
surface area that Tier 0 numerics must expose.

Stage1 storage model:

The bootstrap Integer type is a signed 64-bit machine word.  All widths
narrower than 64 bits are stored in a single Integer with the value
already reduced into its canonical range:

  Int8     range -128 .. 127            stored as signed Integer
  Int16    range -32768 .. 32767        stored as signed Integer
  Int32    range -2^31 .. 2^31-1        stored as signed Integer
  Int64    range -2^63 .. 2^63-1        stored as signed Integer (native)
  UInt8    range 0 .. 255               stored as non-negative Integer
  UInt16   range 0 .. 65535             stored as non-negative Integer
  UInt32   range 0 .. 2^32-1            stored as non-negative Integer
  UInt64   range 0 .. 2^64-1            stored as 2-limb buffer (pointer)
  Int128   range -2^127 .. 2^127-1      stored as 2-limb buffer (pointer)
  UInt128  range 0 .. 2^128-1           stored as 2-limb buffer (pointer)

The "limb buffer" representation for 64+ bit unsigned and 128-bit widths
is a heap allocation of two 64-bit slots in little-endian order:

   slot 0 = bits 0..63    (low limb)
   slot 8 = bits 64..127  (high limb, unused for UInt64)

All UInt64 / Int128 / UInt128 procs in this module either accept a
caller-provided 16-byte buffer or allocate fresh storage via
Layout.allocate and document the lifetime.

This module never reaches outside its public surface for arithmetic;
the wider operations are implemented in terms of 32-bit halves to
sidestep stage1's signed-overflow exposure on raw 64-bit multiply.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/bitwise_core.runa" as Bitwise

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Width Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant INT8_MIN as Integer is -128
Constant INT8_MAX as Integer is 127
Constant INT16_MIN as Integer is -32768
Constant INT16_MAX as Integer is 32767
Constant INT32_MIN as Integer is -2147483648
Constant INT32_MAX as Integer is 2147483647
Constant INT64_MIN as Integer is -9223372036854775808
Constant INT64_MAX as Integer is 9223372036854775807

Constant UINT8_MAX as Integer is 255
Constant UINT16_MAX as Integer is 65535
Constant UINT32_MAX as Integer is 4294967295

Note: 2^32 used as a half-base in extended-precision multiply.
Constant TWO_POW_32 as Integer is 4294967296

Note: Low-32 mask for splitting a 64-bit value into two 32-bit halves.
Constant LOW32_MASK as Integer is 4294967295

Constant CHECKED_OK as Integer is 0
Constant CHECKED_OVERFLOW as Integer is 1
Constant CHECKED_UNDERFLOW as Integer is 2
Constant CHECKED_DIVZERO as Integer is 3

Note: ============================================================================
Note: 8-bit Signed Operations (Int8)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "int8_in_range" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Predicate testing whether an Integer fits the canonical Int8 range.
    Used by every Int8 constructor to enforce the range invariant before
    we commit to the canonical representation.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single double-bounded comparison against INT8_MIN and INT8_MAX.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1), branchless on common ISAs.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    No allocation, no side effects, safe on arbitrary Integer input.
    @End Security_Scope

    If value is less than INT8_MIN:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is greater than INT8_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "int8_truncate" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Truncates an arbitrary Integer to its canonical Int8 value using
    modular arithmetic over 2^8 with sign extension from bit 7.  This is
    the standard "wrapping" reduction used by every checked-overflow
    routine when overflow is permitted to wrap.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Mask to 8 bits, then sign-extend if bit 7 is set.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total over Integer; produces a canonical Int8 for every input.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let low be value modulo by 256
    If low is less than 0:
        Set low to low plus 256
    End If
    If low is greater than 127:
        Return low minus 256
    End If
    Return low
End Process

Process called "int8_add" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Wrapping Int8 addition.  Operands are assumed canonical; the result
    is the modular-2^8 sum sign-extended back into Int8 range.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Add the two Integers in native 64-bit space (no possible overflow at
    that width for values bounded by INT8_MAX), then re-canonicalize.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    No undefined behavior; wrap is well-defined.
    @End Security_Scope

    Return int8_truncate(a plus b)
End Process

Process called "int8_sub" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Wrapping Int8 subtraction.  Mirrors int8_add.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    a minus b in 64-bit space, canonicalize.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Wrap is well-defined.
    @End Security_Scope

    Return int8_truncate(a minus b)
End Process

Process called "int8_mul" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Wrapping Int8 multiplication.  Both inputs are within +/-128 so the
    intermediate product fits 16 bits and cannot overflow the native
    Integer.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Native multiply, then canonicalize.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Wrap is well-defined.
    @End Security_Scope

    Return int8_truncate(a multiplied by b)
End Process

Process called "int8_div" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Truncated-toward-zero Int8 division.  The only special-case is
    INT8_MIN / -1 which overflows the signed range and is canonicalized
    to INT8_MIN per the wrapping convention.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Native divide after handling the two pathological cases.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Division by zero returns 0 to remain total; callers needing a fault
    must use int8_div_checked.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If a is equal to INT8_MIN:
        If b is equal to -1:
            Return INT8_MIN
        End If
    End If
    Return int8_truncate(a divided by b)
End Process

Process called "int8_mod" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Int8 remainder using truncated division.  Result carries the sign of
    the dividend.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Native modulo after handling divide-by-zero.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Mod-by-zero returns 0 to remain total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return int8_truncate(a modulo by b)
End Process

Process called "int8_neg" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Negation with wrap on INT8_MIN.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    0 minus a, then canonicalize.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total; INT8_MIN negates to itself by the wrap rule.
    @End Security_Scope

    Return int8_truncate(0 minus a)
End Process

Process called "int8_abs" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Absolute value with wrap on INT8_MIN.  INT8_MIN absolute is INT8_MIN
    under the wrapping convention.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Branch on sign.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is less than 0:
        Return int8_truncate(0 minus a)
    End If
    Return a
End Process

Process called "int8_min" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Smaller of two Int8 values by signed comparison.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single branch.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    End If
    Return b
End Process

Process called "int8_max" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Larger of two Int8 values by signed comparison.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single branch.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is greater than b:
        Return a
    End If
    Return b
End Process

Process called "int8_clamp" takes value as Integer, lo as Integer, hi as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constrains value to the closed interval [lo, hi].  Bounds are
    expected canonical; no swap is performed if lo > hi (callers must
    pass ordered bounds).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Two branches.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If value is less than lo:
        Return lo
    End If
    If value is greater than hi:
        Return hi
    End If
    Return value
End Process

Process called "int8_add_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checked addition.  Returns the wrapped result and writes a status
    code (CHECKED_OK / CHECKED_OVERFLOW / CHECKED_UNDERFLOW) into the
    Integer pointed to by out_status.  Overflow is detected by comparing
    the 64-bit sum to the Int8 range.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Compute sum at full width, classify, then truncate.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).  One extra comparison versus the wrapping form.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_status pointer must be 0 (no status reporting) or point to
    writable Integer storage.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let sum be a plus b
    Let status be CHECKED_OK
    If sum is greater than INT8_MAX:
        Set status to CHECKED_OVERFLOW
    End If
    If sum is less than INT8_MIN:
        Set status to CHECKED_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return int8_truncate(sum)
End Process

Process called "int8_sub_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checked subtraction.  See int8_add_checked.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Same pattern as add, with subtraction.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_status pointer must be 0 or writable Integer storage.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let diff be a minus b
    Let status be CHECKED_OK
    If diff is greater than INT8_MAX:
        Set status to CHECKED_OVERFLOW
    End If
    If diff is less than INT8_MIN:
        Set status to CHECKED_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return int8_truncate(diff)
End Process

Process called "int8_mul_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checked multiplication.  Intermediate product fits 16 bits so we can
    classify against the Int8 range without further widening.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Native multiply, classify, truncate.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_status pointer must be 0 or writable Integer storage.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let product be a multiplied by b
    Let status be CHECKED_OK
    If product is greater than INT8_MAX:
        Set status to CHECKED_OVERFLOW
    End If
    If product is less than INT8_MIN:
        Set status to CHECKED_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return int8_truncate(product)
End Process

Process called "int8_div_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checked division.  Reports CHECKED_DIVZERO for b == 0 and
    CHECKED_OVERFLOW for INT8_MIN / -1.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Inspect divisor and the INT8_MIN/-1 corner before dividing.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_status pointer must be 0 or writable Integer storage.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, CHECKED_DIVZERO)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If a is equal to INT8_MIN:
        If b is equal to -1:
            If out_status is not equal to 0:
                Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, CHECKED_OVERFLOW)
            End If
            Return INT8_MIN
        End If
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, CHECKED_OK)
    End If
    Return a divided by b
End Process

Process called "int8_and" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bitwise AND on the canonical 8-bit representation.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Mask both operands to 8 bits via UInt-domain AND, then sign-extend.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_and(au, bu)
    If r is greater than 127:
        Return r minus 256
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int8_or" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bitwise OR on the canonical 8-bit representation.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    UInt-domain OR, then sign-extend.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_or(au, bu)
    If r is greater than 127:
        Return r minus 256
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int8_xor" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bitwise XOR on the canonical 8-bit representation.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    UInt-domain XOR, then sign-extend.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_xor(au, bu)
    If r is greater than 127:
        Return r minus 256
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int8_not" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bitwise complement on the 8-bit representation.  Equivalent to
    -a - 1 mod 256 with sign extension.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    XOR with the all-ones byte mask, then sign-extend.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_xor(au, 255)
    If r is greater than 127:
        Return r minus 256
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int8_shl" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Logical left shift.  Counts >= 8 produce zero.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Mask the operand to 8 bits, left shift, re-truncate.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Negative or >=8 counts yield zero, matching Runa's well-defined
    shift convention.
    @End Security_Scope

    If count is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If count is greater than 7:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let shifted be Bitwise.left_shift(au, count)
    Let masked be Bitwise.bitwise_and(shifted, 255)
    If masked is greater than 127:
        Return masked minus 256
    End If
    Return masked
End Process

Process called "int8_shr" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Arithmetic right shift (sign-preserving).  Counts >= 8 reproduce the
    sign bit replicated across all 8 bits.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Native arithmetic right shift on the sign-extended value, clamping
    the count to a safe range.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Negative counts return the input unchanged; counts >= 8 saturate at
    the sign bit.
    @End Security_Scope

    If count is less than 0:
        Return a
    End If
    Let c be count
    If c is greater than 7:
        Set c to 7
    End If
    Let r be Bitwise.right_shift(a, c)
    Return int8_truncate(r)
End Process

Process called "int8_rotl" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Left rotation across 8 bits.  Count is reduced modulo 8.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Mask, then OR the shifted-left part with the shifted-right part.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let c be count modulo by 8
    If c is less than 0:
        Set c to c plus 8
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        If au is greater than 127:
            Return au minus 256
        End If
        Return au
    End If
    Let left be Bitwise.bitwise_and(Bitwise.left_shift(au, c), 255)
    Let right be Bitwise.right_shift_logical(au, 8 minus c)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_or(left, right)
    If r is greater than 127:
        Return r minus 256
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int8_rotr" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Right rotation across 8 bits.  Count is reduced modulo 8.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Implemented in terms of int8_rotl.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let c be count modulo by 8
    If c is less than 0:
        Set c to c plus 8
    End If
    Return int8_rotl(a, 8 minus c modulo by 8)
End Process

Process called "int8_eq" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int8_ne" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is not equal to b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int8_lt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int8_le" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return 1
    End If
    If a is equal to b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int8_gt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int8_ge" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
        Return 1
    End If
    If a is equal to b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int8_pack_be" takes a as Integer, out_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes the canonical UInt8 form of a into the byte at out_buffer.
    Big-endian and little-endian coincide for a single byte; the
    function name distinguishes intent for callers.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single byte store.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_buffer must be writable for at least one byte.
    @End Security_Scope

    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, 0, uint8_truncate(a))
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "int8_pack_le" takes a as Integer, out_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Little-endian byte write (identical to big-endian at 1 byte).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single byte store.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_buffer must be writable for at least one byte.
    @End Security_Scope

    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, 0, uint8_truncate(a))
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "int8_unpack_be" takes buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads one byte and sign-extends into Int8.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single byte load, sign-extend.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    buffer must contain at least one readable byte.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let byte be Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, 0)
    If byte is greater than 127:
        Return byte minus 256
    End If
    Return byte
End Process

Process called "int8_unpack_le" takes buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Identical to int8_unpack_be at 1 byte; named for symmetry.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single byte load, sign-extend.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    buffer must contain at least one readable byte.
    @End Security_Scope

    Return int8_unpack_be(buffer)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: 8-bit Unsigned Operations (UInt8)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "uint8_in_range" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Range predicate for UInt8.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Bounds check against 0 and UINT8_MAX.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If value is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is greater than UINT8_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "uint8_truncate" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Canonical UInt8 reduction modulo 256, returning a value in [0, 255].
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Modulo 256 with bias correction for negative inputs.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total over Integer.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let r be value modulo by 256
    If r is less than 0:
        Set r to r plus 256
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "uint8_add" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return uint8_truncate(a plus b)
End Process

Process called "uint8_sub" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return uint8_truncate(a minus b)
End Process

Process called "uint8_mul" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return uint8_truncate(a multiplied by b)
End Process

Process called "uint8_div" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    Return au divided by bu
End Process

Process called "uint8_mod" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    Return au modulo by bu
End Process

Process called "uint8_min" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    If au is less than bu:
        Return au
    End If
    Return bu
End Process

Process called "uint8_max" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    If au is greater than bu:
        Return au
    End If
    Return bu
End Process

Process called "uint8_clamp" takes value as Integer, lo as Integer, hi as Integer returns Integer:
    Let v be uint8_truncate(value)
    Let l be uint8_truncate(lo)
    Let h be uint8_truncate(hi)
    If v is less than l:
        Return l
    End If
    If v is greater than h:
        Return h
    End If
    Return v
End Process

Process called "uint8_add_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    Let sum be au plus bu
    Let status be CHECKED_OK
    If sum is greater than UINT8_MAX:
        Set status to CHECKED_OVERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return uint8_truncate(sum)
End Process

Process called "uint8_sub_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    Let status be CHECKED_OK
    If au is less than bu:
        Set status to CHECKED_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return uint8_truncate(au minus bu)
End Process

Process called "uint8_mul_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    Let product be au multiplied by bu
    Let status be CHECKED_OK
    If product is greater than UINT8_MAX:
        Set status to CHECKED_OVERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return uint8_truncate(product)
End Process

Process called "uint8_div_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    If bu is equal to 0:
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, CHECKED_DIVZERO)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, CHECKED_OK)
    End If
    Return au divided by bu
End Process

Process called "uint8_and" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return Bitwise.bitwise_and(uint8_truncate(a), uint8_truncate(b))
End Process

Process called "uint8_or" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return Bitwise.bitwise_or(uint8_truncate(a), uint8_truncate(b))
End Process

Process called "uint8_xor" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return Bitwise.bitwise_xor(uint8_truncate(a), uint8_truncate(b))
End Process

Process called "uint8_not" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    Return Bitwise.bitwise_xor(uint8_truncate(a), 255)
End Process

Process called "uint8_shl" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    If count is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If count is greater than 7:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Bitwise.bitwise_and(Bitwise.left_shift(uint8_truncate(a), count), 255)
End Process

Process called "uint8_shr" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    If count is less than 0:
        Return uint8_truncate(a)
    End If
    If count is greater than 7:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Bitwise.right_shift_logical(uint8_truncate(a), count)
End Process

Process called "uint8_rotl" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let c be count modulo by 8
    If c is less than 0:
        Set c to c plus 8
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return au
    End If
    Let left be Bitwise.bitwise_and(Bitwise.left_shift(au, c), 255)
    Let right be Bitwise.right_shift_logical(au, 8 minus c)
    Return Bitwise.bitwise_or(left, right)
End Process

Process called "uint8_rotr" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be count modulo by 8
    If c is less than 0:
        Set c to c plus 8
    End If
    Let inv be (8 minus c) modulo by 8
    Return uint8_rotl(a, inv)
End Process

Process called "uint8_eq" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If uint8_truncate(a) is equal to uint8_truncate(b):
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "uint8_ne" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If uint8_truncate(a) is not equal to uint8_truncate(b):
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "uint8_lt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If uint8_truncate(a) is less than uint8_truncate(b):
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "uint8_le" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    If au is less than bu:
        Return 1
    End If
    If au is equal to bu:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "uint8_gt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If uint8_truncate(a) is greater than uint8_truncate(b):
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "uint8_ge" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint8_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint8_truncate(b)
    If au is greater than bu:
        Return 1
    End If
    If au is equal to bu:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "uint8_pack_be" takes a as Integer, out_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, 0, uint8_truncate(a))
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "uint8_pack_le" takes a as Integer, out_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, 0, uint8_truncate(a))
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "uint8_unpack_be" takes buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    Return Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, 0)
End Process

Process called "uint8_unpack_le" takes buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    Return Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, 0)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: 16-bit Operations (Int16 / UInt16)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "int16_in_range" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is less than INT16_MIN:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is greater than INT16_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "int16_truncate" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Canonical Int16 reduction mod 65536 with sign extension from bit 15.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Modulo, bias, sign-extend.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let low be value modulo by 65536
    If low is less than 0:
        Set low to low plus 65536
    End If
    If low is greater than 32767:
        Return low minus 65536
    End If
    Return low
End Process

Process called "uint16_in_range" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is greater than UINT16_MAX:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "uint16_truncate" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let r be value modulo by 65536
    If r is less than 0:
        Set r to r plus 65536
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int16_add" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return int16_truncate(a plus b)
End Process

Process called "int16_sub" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return int16_truncate(a minus b)
End Process

Process called "int16_mul" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Return int16_truncate(a multiplied by b)
End Process

Process called "int16_div" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If a is equal to INT16_MIN:
        If b is equal to -1:
            Return INT16_MIN
        End If
    End If
    Return int16_truncate(a divided by b)
End Process

Process called "int16_mod" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return int16_truncate(a modulo by b)
End Process

Process called "int16_neg" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    Return int16_truncate(0 minus a)
End Process

Process called "int16_abs" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than 0:
        Return int16_truncate(0 minus a)
    End If
    Return a
End Process

Process called "int16_min" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    End If
    Return b
End Process

Process called "int16_max" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
        Return a
    End If
    Return b
End Process

Process called "int16_clamp" takes value as Integer, lo as Integer, hi as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is less than lo:
        Return lo
    End If
    If value is greater than hi:
        Return hi
    End If
    Return value
End Process

Process called "int16_add_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    Let sum be a plus b
    Let status be CHECKED_OK
    If sum is greater than INT16_MAX:
        Set status to CHECKED_OVERFLOW
    End If
    If sum is less than INT16_MIN:
        Set status to CHECKED_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return int16_truncate(sum)
End Process

Process called "int16_sub_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    Let diff be a minus b
    Let status be CHECKED_OK
    If diff is greater than INT16_MAX:
        Set status to CHECKED_OVERFLOW
    End If
    If diff is less than INT16_MIN:
        Set status to CHECKED_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return int16_truncate(diff)
End Process

Process called "int16_mul_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    Let product be a multiplied by b
    Let status be CHECKED_OK
    If product is greater than INT16_MAX:
        Set status to CHECKED_OVERFLOW
    End If
    If product is less than INT16_MIN:
        Set status to CHECKED_UNDERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return int16_truncate(product)
End Process

Process called "int16_div_checked" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, CHECKED_DIVZERO)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If a is equal to INT16_MIN:
        If b is equal to -1:
            If out_status is not equal to 0:
                Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, CHECKED_OVERFLOW)
            End If
            Return INT16_MIN
        End If
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, CHECKED_OK)
    End If
    Return a divided by b
End Process

Process called "int16_and" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint16_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint16_truncate(b)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_and(au, bu)
    If r is greater than 32767:
        Return r minus 65536
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int16_or" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint16_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint16_truncate(b)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_or(au, bu)
    If r is greater than 32767:
        Return r minus 65536
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int16_xor" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint16_truncate(a)
    Let bu be uint16_truncate(b)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_xor(au, bu)
    If r is greater than 32767:
        Return r minus 65536
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int16_not" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint16_truncate(a)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_xor(au, 65535)
    If r is greater than 32767:
        Return r minus 65536
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int16_shl" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    If count is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If count is greater than 15:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let au be uint16_truncate(a)
    Let shifted be Bitwise.left_shift(au, count)
    Let masked be Bitwise.bitwise_and(shifted, 65535)
    If masked is greater than 32767:
        Return masked minus 65536
    End If
    Return masked
End Process

Process called "int16_shr" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    If count is less than 0:
        Return a
    End If
    Let c be count
    If c is greater than 15:
        Set c to 15
    End If
    Return int16_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift(a, c))
End Process

Process called "int16_rotl" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    Let au be uint16_truncate(a)
    Let c be count modulo by 16
    If c is less than 0:
        Set c to c plus 16
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        If au is greater than 32767:
            Return au minus 65536
        End If
        Return au
    End If
    Let left be Bitwise.bitwise_and(Bitwise.left_shift(au, c), 65535)
    Let right be Bitwise.right_shift_logical(au, 16 minus c)
    Let r be Bitwise.bitwise_or(left, right)
    If r is greater than 32767:
        Return r minus 65536
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "int16_rotr" takes a as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be count modulo by 16
    If c is less than 0:
        Set c to c plus 16
    End If
    Let inv be (16 minus c) modulo by 16
    Return int16_rotl(a, inv)
End Process

Process called "int16_eq" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int16_ne" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is not equal to b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int16_lt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int16_le" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return 1
    End If
    If a is equal to b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int16_gt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int16_ge" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
        Return 1
    End If
    If a is equal to b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "int16_pack_be" takes a as Integer, out_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Big-endian pack: high byte first, low byte second.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Mask and store two bytes.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_buffer must have 2 bytes writable.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let v be uint16_truncate(a)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, 0, Bitwise.right_shift_logical(v, 8))
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, 1, Bitwise.bitwise_and(v, 255))
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "int16_pack_le" takes a as Integer, out_buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Little-endian pack: low byte first, high byte second.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Mask and store two bytes.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_buffer must have 2 bytes writable.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let v be uint16_truncate(a)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, 0, Bitwise.bitwise_and(v, 255))
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, 1, Bitwise.right_shift_logical(v, 8))
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "int16_unpack_be" takes buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hi be Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, 0)
    Let lo be Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, 1)
    Let v be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(hi, 8), lo)
    If v is greater than 32767:
        Return v minus 65536
    End If
    Return v
End Process

Process called "int16_unpack_le" takes buffer as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lo be Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, 0)
    Let hi be Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, 1)
    Let v be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(hi, 8), lo)
    If v is greater than 32767:
        Return v minus 65536
    End If
    Return v
End Process

