Process called "uint128_from_int" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Converts a non-negative Integer to a fresh UInt128.  Negative values
    are reduced modulo 2^128 by zeroing the high limb regardless (the
    caller is responsible for explicit sign handling on unsigned types).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate; store value in low limb; zero high limb.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let buf be uint128_alloc()
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(buf, I128_LIMB_LO_OFF, value)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(buf, I128_LIMB_HI_OFF, 0)
    Return buf
End Process

